  sodium: 450 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/roasted-pork-tenderloin-5e5e9a1bba47be36e310dceb
course: main course
cuisine: North America
time required: 30 minutes
servings: 2
author: HelloFresh
---

Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Dice @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces; toss on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Roast on top rack, tossing halfway through, until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve, peel, and dice @Yellow Onion{1}(peeled and diced) into ½-inch pieces. Mince or grate @Garlic{2%cloves}(minced). Halve @Lemon{1}. Trim and halve @Zucchini{1} lengthwise; slice crosswise into ½-inchthick half-moons. Roughly chop @Cilantro{1/4%ounce}(roughly chopped).

Pat @Pork Tenderloin{12%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add pork and sear, turning occasionally, until browned all over, ~{4-8%minutes} total. Turn off heat.

Toss onion and zucchini on one side of a second baking sheet with a drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Transfer pork to empty side. Roast on middle rack until veggies are tender and pork is cooked through, ~{10-12%minutes}. Let pork rest ~{5%minutes} after removing from oven.

> Tip: If veggies finish cooking first, remove from sheet and continue cooking pork.

Meanwhile, melt @Butter{1%tablespoon} in pan used for pork over medium-high heat. Add garlic and cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}. Stir in @Chicken Demi-Glace{1} and @water{1/4%cup}, scraping up any browned bits from bottom of pan. Simmer until slightly reduced, ~{3-4%minutes}. Turn off heat. Season with @pepper{to taste} and a squeeze of lemon juice.

Divide potatoes, onion, and zucchini between plates. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}; top with a squeeze of lemon juice to taste. Slice pork crosswise, then arrange on top of potatoes and veggies. Drizzle with pan sauce and garnish with cilantro.